description:
**ABA A Step At A Time Care** is a caring, outcomes-driven, evidence-based provider of Applied Behavior Analysis for children with autism spectrum disorder and related disorders in Connecticut and the New York City area. We are parent-owned and clinician-led. We are scaling and searching for passionate clinicians to carry out our mission of delivering best-in-class services to children with special needs. Our goal is support our clinicians every day so they may focus 100% of their time on their passion. Give us a call at (917) 284-9393 or email your resume to: info@abaastepatatimecare.com. We can't wait to get to know you!

**Location:**

We are looking for a talented and compassionate BT or RBT within access to Midtown Manhattan for an immediate or prompt start.

**Responsibilities:**

o Conduct direct implementation of skill and behavior plans developed by BCBA and assist with the plan development when appropriate;

o Collect and record data accurately and efficiently;

o Train new and existing staff members in behavior-analytic strategies;

o Communicate clearly and effectively;

o Abide by the code of ethics for Registered Behavior Technicians;

o Maintain confidentiality and respect for clients;

o Continue professional development.

**Qualifications:**

* RBT certification is a plus;
* Experience in the field of autism and ABA;
* Experience in scope and sequence of early learning curriculum;
* Experience in building trust with patients, families, and other team members working in ABA or in other disciplines.

**ABA A Step At A Time Care Offers:**

* Hourly wage commensurate with experience;
* Long-term employment and career growth;
* Exciting opportunity to grow with a high potential provider group;
* Paid drive time;
* Paid professional development;
* Staff incentive stipend;
* Collaborative environment;
* Individual and group supervision.

ABA A Step At A Time Care provides equal employment opportunity to all individuals regardless of race, color, creed, religion, gender, age, sexual orientation, national origin, disability, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by state, federal, or local law. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.

Job Types: Full-time, Part-time

Pay: $25.00 - $32.00 per hour

Expected hours: 25 per week

Benefits:

* 401(k)
* Dental insurance
* Flexible schedule
* Health insurance
* Paid time off
* Professional development assistance
* Referral program
* Retirement plan
* Vision insurance

Medical Specialty:

* Pediatrics

Schedule:

* After school
* Monday to Friday
* Weekends as needed

Work Location: In person
